cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the role of caching in networking systems and proposes a new cache replacement policy for video streaming applications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a modification to the LRU strategy for cache replacement. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper discusses the application of the proposed cache replacement policy to video streaming and evaluates its performance in terms of stall durations. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of the proposed cache replacement policy on the overall system performance. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on security or cryptography, but it may be relevant in the context of secure video streaming applications.
